To reiterate its commitment to providing consumers with amazing gadgets, the leading multinational computer and electronics company, Asus, has launched its ZenBook 14X OLED Space Edition for Nigerians. Revealed during a launch event held on Wednesday, the ZenBook 14X OLED Space Edition is a super device that is said to have been inspired by the celestial bodies. The design elements of the Zenbook 14X OLED Space Edition are heavily influenced by the history of space travel. Patterned like a MIR Station and morse code, with curved lines representing the celestial capsule, the dots on the cover of the ZenBook 14X has the Latin phrase “Ad Astra Per Aspera”, which means “Through the hardships to the Stars.” Asus calls the cover of the ASUS Zenbook 14X OLED Space Edition “ZenVision”. It features the exclusive ZenVision display which is inspired by a spaceship’s datasheet. The ZenVision display is a 3.5-inch OLED panel that supports 256 x 64 resolution and 150-nit brightness. In line with the space theme, the 2.9-pound ZenBook 14X was said to have passed some Space-Grade standard tests and met the ultra-demanding MIL-STD-810H U.S. military standard for reliability and durability. The Vibration test of the Space-Grade standard is up to 2000 Hz, and the temperature test is a greater temperature difference than the general military regulations. The laptop can operate stably in environments with a very large temperature difference. Heat affects performance and in a country like Nigeria where the climate is tropical, the ASUS ZenBook 14X OLED Space Edition is said to always stay cool. ASUS boasts of using a highly efficient dual-fan cooling system that incorporates two heat pipes. The advanced cooling design of the ASUS ZenBook 14X OLED Space Edition allows the CPU TDP to reach 45W and ensures that the system stays cool and provides maximum performance, anytime and anywhere. The ASUS ZenBook 14X OLED Space Edition features a 14-inch 16:10 OLED touchscreen. The display supports 2880 x 1800 resolution, 90 Hz refresh rate and 0.2 ms response time. The ASUS ZenBook 14X OLED Space Edition is powered by the latest generation Intel Core H-series processors paired with up to 32GB LPDDR5 memory and 1TB PCIe 4.0×4 NVMe M.2 SSD, providing users higher computing performance. POLL Characterized by its 2.8K OLED Display with 100% DCI-P3 colour gamut, the ASUS ZenVision, design elements of space, space-grade reliability, new hardware and iceCool thermal technology are some of the features that stand the Zenbook 14X out. ASUS affirms its passion for technology and drives for innovation while dreaming, daring, and striving to create an effortless and joyful digital life for everyone. With incredible ideas and experiences, the company said it aspires to deliver the incredible in everything it does.